refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
public intDirectoryIterator::getMTime
Get the last modification time of the current DirectoryIterator item, as a Unix timestamp.

  &reftitle.examples;



    A DirectoryIterator::getMTime example


      Displays a list of the files in the directory of the script
      and their last modified times.



<?php
$iterator = new DirectoryIterator(dirname(__FILE__));
foreach ($iterator as $fileinfo) {
    if ($fileinfo->isFile()) {
        echo $fileinfo->getFilename() . " " . $fileinfo->getMTime() . "\n";
    }
}
?>


    &example.outputs.similar;


apple.jpg 1240047118
banana.jpg 1240065176
index.php 1240047208
pear.jpg 12240047979
